{
  "stem": "9701.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was called That's D-E-R, and then a new word, S-T-U-umlaut-R-M-E-R.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I-- my parents had told me to not go over there and read that paper.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If I walk past that building, just walk past and don't look at it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And of course, I did look at it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I remember seeing horrible, ugly caricatures of Jews with big, hooked noses, and being fat and hunchbacked, and being greedy.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I knew that that had something to do with Hitler.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The next major event that really brought anti-Semitism to my attention, though I may not have been able to call it anti-Semitism at that time, was in 1935.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My parents had decided that I should attend school in a neighboring community, because the educational level in that school was higher.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was called a Real Gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That's capital R-E-A-L G-Y-M-N-A-S-I-U-M.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I went with my father to be enrolled.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the principal said, I'm sorry, but Hedy can't come to school here, because you're Jewish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And my father, without saying a word, pointed to a pin that he always wore very proudly in the lapel of his jacket.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the principal said, I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I didn't realize that you are a wounded veteran of World War I.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "In that case, Hedy can come to school here.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And when I started in that school, there were several Jewish children in the-- in the school, a number of them from my own community.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But over the next few years, the number of Jewish children decreased, to the point when I left that school several years later, there was only one other Jewish child and I in that school.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
